subSubSection.paragraph:
Other Saudi Arabian records: Al-Qassim Region : Buraidah ( Dabbour 1979a , b); Al-Baha Region : Jabal Shada al-A’la Nature Reserve (
El-Hawagry et al . 2016
); Asir Region : Garf Raydah Nature Reserve (
El-Hawagry et al . 2017
); Abha, Madinat al-Ameer Sultan ( Dawah & Abdullah 2006 ); Makkah Region : Al Shumisy (Dabbour & El- Dawy 1981); Riyadh Region : Rawdhat Khorim National Park (
El-Hawagry et al . 2019
).

Remarks. This species has been reared from decaying matter in damaged egg pods of desert locusts
Schistocerca gregaria (Forskål 1775)
in Eritrea ( Greathead 1963 , as Acocetor [sic];
Stower et al. 1958
) and from domestic cat dung in Israel ( Dikow & Mathis 2002 ). This species has been found in sandy areas with little or no vegetation that were surrounded by or close to grass-covered habitats with organic debris or garbage that had accumulated at the high tide mark on sandy beaches ( Dikow & Mathis 2002 ; Mathis & Zatwarnicki 2003 ). Dikow & Mathis (2002) have given some observations on the mating behaviour of this species.
